cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with UAV-mounted flying base stations providing data communication services to radio nodes on the ground. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with trajectory optimization of UAVs. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimal channel parameter learning. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper deals with node scheduling algorithms. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with intelligent IoT data harvesting.
